2026-04-16 12:39:37 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['ambient sensor module internal 0 V output reference connection / wiring', 'ambient sensor module external − output terminal / cable connection'] hypothesis_explanation='Measurements show the power‑supply outputs +12 V and 0 V correctly and this +12 V reaches the ambient sensor module relay input and its + output terminal. The relay output is continuous with the external + output cable. However, at the load and at the sensor module output we only see ~0.12–0.36 V, implying that the return (0 V) path from the ambient sensor module to the load and to the measurement reference is not actually bonded to the true 0 V of the power supply. This indicates an open or high‑impedance fault on the ambient sensor module’s negative/ground output path—either internal wiring from the module’s internal 0 V reference to the external − output terminal, or the external − output connector/cable itself. With the + side present but the − side floating, the load and measurement points sit near 0 V with only leakage-level voltages, which matches the observations. Replacing/repairing the internal 0 V output reference connection and/or the external − terminal/cable of the ambient sensor module should restore a solid return path and allow the full 12 V to appear across the load, eliminating the fault.'
