Instruction: Using the multimeter, in the dark condition, directly measure the DC voltage between the ambient sensor module’s external + output terminal and its external − output terminal (i.e., across the two output cables themselves). Then, still at the sensor module, measure voltage between the internal ground/0 V node used by the relay and logic (the point used as “ground” for the earlier 0.12 V measurement) and the external − output terminal. Also measure between that same internal ground node and the external − input terminal from the power supply. This will reveal whether the internal reference point is floating above the true system 0 V and by how much, and whether the module is referencing the wrong conductor as ground.
