Instruction: With power on in the dark condition, use a multimeter to measure DC voltage at both terminals of the ambient sensor module’s ‘switched cables indicator’ LED relative to the PSU − line, and also directly across the LED. Determine whether this LED ever sees ~12 V or a normal forward bias when the relay is supposed to be closed. If there is 12 V on the relay input but the indicator LED never gets forward biased (stays near 0 V or only a few hundred mV), this will confirm an open circuit or incorrect connection between the relay output node and the rest of the output‑path wiring (indicator LED and external + terminal).
