- main_bulb: Main Load (lamp) [inside enclosure: cube_load]
- internal_bulb: Internal Indicator Lamp [inside enclosure: cube_load] [NOTE: This lamp is connected in parallel with the main load and reflects voltage conditions across that branch.]
- load_diode: Load Protection Diode [inside enclosure: cube_load]
- load_cable_pos: Load Input Cable (+)
- load_cable_neg: Load Input Cable (−)

Instruction: With the ambient sensor module output plug disconnected from the load module, use an ohmmeter to re-measure resistance between the load module’s + and − input pins, then measure from + input to chassis/box and from − input to chassis/box. Next, with the load module still isolated, apply 12 V directly from the power‑supply module to the load module inputs (correct polarity) and observe whether the main lamp and internal indicator lamp illuminate steadily. This will determine whether the 1.5 Ω path between + and − is intrinsic to the load module or due to the control‑module side, and whether the load module itself operates normally when driven directly.
