description: With power on in the dark, place the multimeter COM lead on the PSU Output Cable (−). Measure DC voltage at three points: (1) PSU Output Cable (+), (2) ambient sensor module relay input terminal, and (3) ambient sensor module relay output terminal / Control Output Cable (+). Then move the COM lead to the ambient sensor module internal reference node (the node tied through 10 kΩ to PSU −) and re‑measure voltages at the relay input and output. Report all six readings so we can reconcile the earlier, partly inconsistent measurements and determine whether the relay output is actually at 12 V or only a few hundred millivolts above true ground., outcome='Measured at PSU Output Cable (+) with COM on PSU (−): 11.9876 V.  \nMeasured at the control relay (relay input / output terminals) with COM on PSU (−): 11.9873 V on the high side and 0.3592 V on the low side, consistently across repeated measurements.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=105.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> ambient sensor module external output connectors and load‑module input cables (polarity and continuity per individual conductor),
description: With power off, disconnect the two‑wire plug pair between the ambient sensor module output and the load module. Using the ohmmeter, first identify on the load module which of its two input pins actually goes to the series diode anode and which goes directly to the lamp return (0 V). Then, on the control module side, identify which output pin is the +12 V from the relay and which is the 0 V reference. Finally, verify conductor‑by‑conductor continuity from each control‑module pin to its mated load‑module pin when the plug is re‑assembled, checking that + goes only to the diode/lamp + node and − only to the lamp return, and that no cross‑connection (+ to − or − to +) exists even if the plug’s polarity labels appear correct., outcome='On the load side, the + input cable goes directly to the load protection diode, and the − input cable goes to the main lamp path (about 96.9 Ω). On the control side, the Control Output Cable (+) goes directly to the control relay, and continuity checks show that Control Output (+) mates to Load Input (+) and Control Output (−) mates to Load Input (−). No POLARITY INVERSION DETECTED; however, there is a low-resistance (~1.5 Ω) resistive path between the (+) and (−) lines in both directions.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=250.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> load module input + and − terminals (with control module disconnected),
description: With the ambient sensor module output plug disconnected from the load module, use an ohmmeter to re-measure resistance between the load module’s + and − input pins, then measure from + input to chassis/box and from − input to chassis/box. Next, with the load module still isolated, apply 12 V directly from the power‑supply module to the load module inputs (correct polarity) and observe whether the main lamp and internal indicator lamp illuminate steadily. This will determine whether the 1.5 Ω path between + and − is intrinsic to the load module or due to the control‑module side, and whether the load module itself operates normally when driven directly., outcome='Load Input Cables (+) and (−) both show nominal continuity at 0.10 Ω.  \nThe load cube enclosure could not be measured for resistance due to lacking a measurable affordance, and the main lamp and internal indicator lamp are both not lit with the present voltages (≈0.36 V on +, ≈0 V on −).\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=145.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> ambient sensor module output + and − terminals (with load disconnected),
description: Disconnect the load module completely. With only the power‑supply feeding the ambient sensor module, measure the DC voltage between the module’s external + output and − output terminals in the dark condition, and also measure the resistance between those two output pins with power off. This will show whether the ~1.5 Ω low‑resistance path and the heavy loading to ~0.36 V originate inside the control module or are still coming from the (supposedly) isolated load side or cabling., outcome='With the load module disconnected, the ambient sensor module’s external outputs are at about 0.36 V on Control Output Cable (+) and near 0 V on Control Output Cable (−). The resistance/continuity of both Control Output Cable (+) and (−) is nominal at approximately 0.10 Ω each.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=80.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
